[SN]TITLE[SN]
Search launched for missing Ammanford pensioner

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A search has been launched for a pensioner who has gone missing in Swansea.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Gordon Culliford, 77, from Ammanford, Carmarthenshire, was last seen at about 13.15 BST on Thursday at the city's Singleton Hospital.
He is white, 5ft 7in tall, with white swept back hair and was last seen wearing black glasses and a red jacket.
South Wales Police said there is "considerable concern" for the man and called or information.
